<img src="boardbios/photos/John_Arthorne.jpg" align="left" style="padding-right: 5px;" width="120">
John has worked on the <a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/Eclipse">Eclipse</a> and <a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/Equinox">Equinox</a> projects for the past
decade in many different areas. He was the main developer on the
resource model for many years, and designed the platform's 
concurrency infrastructure. In recent years he has focused on
the <a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/Orion">Orion project</a>, provisioning (<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/P2">p2</a>), <a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/E4">e4</a>, and overall platform
<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/API_Central">API quality</a>. John is a member of the <a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/Architecture_Council">Eclipse Architecture Council</a>,
<a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/Planning_Council">Planning Council</a>, <a href="http://wiki.eclipse.org/Eclipse/PMC">Eclipse Project PMC</a>, and the <a href="http://www.eclipse.org/org/foundation/directors.php">Eclipse Foundation
Board of Directors</a>. John is a Senior Software Developer at IBM,
based in Ottawa, Canada.